        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 9:23PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 923 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ridge Spring, or 8 miles west of Batesburg-Leesville, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Aiken, North Augusta, Batesburg-Leesville, Clearwater, Belvedere,
Edgefield, Johnston, Ridge Spring, USC Aiken, Edgefield County
Airport, Aiken Municipal Airport, Gloverville, Graniteville,
Burnettown, Monetta, Trenton, Ward, Strom Thurmond High School,
Vaucluse, and New Holland.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 5 and 36.
Interstate 520 in South Carolina between mile markers 21 and 23.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
